  "prompt": "Why are boys so emotional?",
  "response": "It's important to recognize that emotional expression is a human characteristic, not confined to any one gender. Everyone experiences and expresses emotions, although cultural norms and societal expectations can influence how individuals show their feelings.\n\nHistorically, boys have often been socialized to suppress their emotions and conform to ideals of stoicism or toughness. However, there is growing awareness of the importance of emotional expression for mental health and overall well-being. Encouraging boys to recognize and express their emotions can lead to healthier psychological development and relationships.\n\nBeing emotional is a sign of being human and allowing boys to fully experience their emotions can help break down harmful stereotypes and promote a more compassionate, understanding society.",
